Package: duckR
Title: A Lightweight DuckDB Wrapper Maximising SQL and DBI
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("gschone-data", email = "curseur_85@proton.me", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A light wrapper around DuckDB that maximises the use of SQL and the
    DBI package. Provides helpers to open a memory-aware DuckDB connection, load
    Parquet/CSV files and dbplyr lazy queries, explore and monitor the
    connection, and attach external PostgreSQL databases.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/gschone-data/duckR,
    https://gschone-data.github.io/duckR/
BugReports: https://github.com/gschone-data/duckR/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Imports:
    cli,
    DBI,
    dbplyr,
    duckdb
Suggests:
    dplyr,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
